@startuml activity-diagram
' Claude Code v2.1.88 вЂ” Activity Diagram
' Main agent loop and key sub-flows

skinparam activityBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam activityBorderColor #555
skinparam activityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam activityDiamondBorderColor #888
skinparam arrowColor #333
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam noteBorderColor #90CAF9
skinparam partitionBackgroundColor #F5F5F5

' в•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ
' MAIN AGENT LOOP
' в•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ

title Claude Code вЂ” Main Agent Loop (query.ts)

|User Input Layer|
start
:User submits prompt;

|Query Engine|
:processUserInput()\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nParse slash commands\nBuild UserMessage\nHandle file attachments;

if (Slash command?) then (yes)
  :Execute command\n(/plan, /config, /login...);
  stop
else (no)
endif

:fetchSystemPromptParts()\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nAssemble system prompt\nInject active tools\nLoad CLAUDE.md memory files\nApply permission rules;

:recordTranscript()\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nPersist user message\nto JSONL on disk;

|Context Management|
loop_start:
:normalizeMessagesForAPI()\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nStrip UI-only fields\nDeduplicate compact markers;

if (Token budget exceeded?) then (yes)
  :autoCompact()\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nSummarize old messages\nvia compact API call\nInsert compact_boundary;
  note right
    Three strategies:
    1. autoCompact (summarize)
    2. snipCompact (trim zombies)
    3. contextCollapse (restructure)
  end note
  goto loop_start
else (no)
endif

|Claude API|
:POST /v1/messages\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nmodel + tools + system prompt\nStreaming enabled\nAbortController attached;

|Stream Processing|
repeat
  if (Stream event type?) then (text delta)
    :Emit text to consumer\n(REPL / SDK);
  else (tool_use block)
    :Buffer tool_use block;
  else (message_stop)
  endif
repeat while (More stream events?) is (yes)
-> no;

|Tool Dispatch|
if (stop_reason?) then (tool_use)

  :StreamingToolExecutor\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nPartition: concurrent vs serial\nSafe in parallel: Glob, Grep, Read\nSerial: Bash, FileEdit, FileWrite;

  |Permission System|
  while (More tools to execute?) is (yes)

    :tool.validateInput(args, context)\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nZod schema + tool-specific rules;

    if (Input valid?) then (no)
      :Append tool_result(error);
    else (yes)

      :Run PreToolUse Hooks\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nUser-defined shell scripts\nCan: approve / deny / modify;

      if (Hook decision?) then (deny)
        :Append tool_result(permission denied);
      else (approve / no hook)

        :Check permission rules\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nalwaysAllowRules в†’ auto-approve\nalwaysDenyRules  в†’ auto-deny\nalwaysAskRules   в†’ force prompt;

        if (Rule match?) then (always allow)
          ' fall through to call
        else if (Rule match?) then (always deny)
          :Append tool_result(denied);
        else (no rule)

          |User Interaction|
          :Show permission dialog\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nTool name + input preview\nAllow Once / Always / Deny;

          if (User decision?) then (deny)
            :Append tool_result(denied);
          else (allow)
          endif
        endif

        if (Permission granted?) then (yes)
          |Tool Execution|
          :tool.checkPermissions()\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nTool-specific logic\n(e.g. path sandboxing);

          if (Tool permission ok?) then (yes)
            :tool.call(args, context)\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nExecute tool logic\nEmit progress events\nReturn ToolResult;

            if (Tool error?) then (yes)
              :Append tool_result(error details);
            else (no)
              :Append tool_result to messages[]\nrecordTranscript();
            end if
          else (no)
            :Append tool_result(denied);
          endif
        endif
      endif
    endif

  endwhile (no)

  |Query Engine|
  if (Abort signal?) then (yes)
    :Emit AbortError;
    stop
  else (no)
    goto loop_start
  endif

else (end_turn)

  :recordTranscript(assistantMessage);

  |User Input Layer|
  :Yield final result message\n(text, usage, cost, session_id);
  stop

endif

@enduml
